<TITLE> Saifur Rahman's son Naser gets 13 years for graft </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 31 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court Monday sentenced former finance minister M Saifur Rahman's elder son Naser Rahnman to a total of 13 years imprisonment on charges of amassing illegal wealth and concealing wealth information from the Anticorruption Commission. Judge Khandaker Kamaluzzaman, of Special Judges' Court-9, also fined Naser Tk 5 lakh and told him failure to pay would result in an additional one year behind bars. The court ordered authorities to confiscate property worth Tk 1.80 crore from the convicted former BNP lawmaker. Naser's sentence comprises two termsthree years for concealing wealth information and 10 years for accumulating illegal wealthwhich are to run consecutively. The sentence is effective from Feb 3, 2007, the day Naser was arrested. The High Court stayed the charges against Naser's wife Rezina Rahnman who was also named in the original case. She is currently on bail. ACC assistant director Md Moniruzzaman filed the case with Gulshan Police Station on May 27 last year. According to the case details, the couple together concealed wealth of Tk 2.63 crore in their wealth statement submitted to the ACC. They were also accused of amassing wealth of Tk 6.23 crore beyond their known sources of income. Following an ACC investigation, the former finance minister's son was eventually charged with amassing illegal wealth of Tk 5.33 crore, and concealing Tk 1.80 crore in his ACC wealth statement. In a separate, a Sylhet court sentenced Naser to nine years imprisonment for extortion on Sept 18 last year. bdnew
